               <head>Shushan ha-refu᾿ah by Bernard de Gordon</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85083148" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>Medical work. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="210v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/226497544">Bernard, de Gordon, 1260-1318</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/226497544">ברנרד דה גורדון</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Shushan ha-refu᾿ah</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">שושן הרפואה</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Yeḳutiel ben Solomon's Hebrew translation of Bernard de Gordon's 'Lilium Medicinae.' The work opens (folio 9r-10r) with a list of chapters, without noting the division to parts. In some instances, wrong numbers have been given to the chapters in the manuscript. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
               <physDesc rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <p>Parchment and paper codex of the 15th century. </p>
                  
                  
                  
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     
                     
                     
                     <supportDesc material="mixed">
                        
                        
                        
                        <support>Parchment and paper. </support>
                        
                        
                        
                        <extent>210 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              
                              
                              
                              <height>250</height>
                              
                              
                              
                              <width>190</width>
                           
                           
                           
                           </dimensions>
                           
                           
                           
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              
                              
                              
                              <height>185</height>
                              
                              
                              
                              <width>130</width>
                           
                           
                           
                           </dimensions>
                        
                        
                        
                        </extent>
                        
                        
                        
                        <foliation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>210 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 2 at the end).
</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </foliation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <collation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>21 quires of originally 10, 8 and 12 leaves each, with parchment used for the two outer and the two inner leaves of a quire in the earlier part, and for the outer leaves only in the latter part. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </collation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <condition>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Losses to damp and mould in parchment and paper, infilled before rebinding. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Tidemarks and mould spotting. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Paling ink. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </condition>
                     
                     
                     
                     </supportDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <layoutDesc>
                        
                        
                        
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31">
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Uniform layout. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Hard-point ruling visible. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Hair side and flesh side of parchment folios distinguishable. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Large square initial words. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Additions and notes on margin largely by the main scribe. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Maniculae, e.g. folios 152v-153v, 155r, 156v, 157r. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </layout>
                     
                     
                     
                     </layoutDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  </objectDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <handDesc hands="3">
                     
                     
                     
                     <summary>Byzantine semi-cursive scripts of the 15th century. </summary>
                     
                     
                     
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <additions>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 1-4 are parchment leaves of the 12th century, containing a portion of Homily IV of St. Chrysostom on Isaiah 6:1. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folio 5 is a paper flyleaf of the 17th to 18th century (partly folded), and contains a short piece in Hebrew dealing with the plague, followed by two pieces in Turkish (in Hebrew characters) on the same subject. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 6-8: notes and scribblings, partly illegible. Shelomoh Martin, perhaps a former owner, mentioned in two entries in connection with money transactions. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 1v-3v and 6r-8v, margins: a Hebrew-Turkish vocabulary, apparently of the 17th century. </p>
                  
                  
                  
                  </additions>
                  
                  
                  
                  <bindingDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <binding>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>BM in-house. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Spine: 'Shushan ha-Re'Phu'ah. Jekuthiel Ben Solomon's Versions of Lilium Medicinae. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 15,455.'</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </binding>
                  
                  
                  
